mods:mods.mods:abstract: A scrapbook of photographs taken by Mr. W.D. Reynolds of Bartlesville, OK during his voyage on the ocean liner Taiyo Maru to Japan, China and Hawaii. During this trip he witnessed the devastation of the Great Kanto earthquake of 1923 as he and his family landed in Japan.
